            <title>[QPID-6205] [0.8/0.9.x] JMS client leaks transport threads and sockets if connection cannot be established to the broker</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-6205</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If timeout occurs on connection establishing attempt in AMQConnectionDelegate_8_0.makeBrokerConnection(BrokerDetails) and AMQTimeoutException(&quot;Server did not respond in a timely fashion&quot;, null) is thrown from StateWaiter, the corresponding network transport object is not closed leaving behind running IoSender and IoReceiver threads and opened client socket&lt;/p&gt;</description>
